type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link> to prove that being <html:span
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml"
style="white-space: nowrap"><fr:tex>n</fr:tex>-truncated</html:span> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>. In other words, we must show that <fr:tex>\mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } \mathsf {isTruncated} \, \mathopen {} \left ( n-1 \right ) \mathclose {} \, A</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
